</span>The Case of Singapore Incorporated”<span style="font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: Times New Roman">
(1996),</span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span>presented at the
&quot;Changes in Firm Boundaries in Response to Government Policy Changes&quot;
session, Sixteenth Annual International Strategic Management Society Conference,
Phoenix, Arizona, November.<o:p>
</o:p>
<br>
<br>
“Singapore Incorporated:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Reinterpreting
Singapore’s Business Environments through a Corporate Metaphor”<span style="font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: Times New Roman">
(1995)</span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">, </span>presented at<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>the 1995 Academy of International Business Annual Conference,
Seoul, South Korea, November (with Linda Low and Mun Heng Toh).<br>
<br>
“The Chameleon in the Cactus Patch:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Managing
Multinational Corporations in Mexico”<span style="font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: Times New Roman">
(1995),</span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: Times New Roman">p</span>resented
at the &quot;Competitive Success in Mexico&quot; session, Fifteenth Annual
International Strategic Management Society Conference, Mexico City, October.<o:p>
</o:p>
<br>
<br>
Session Chair (1995) “Competitive Success in Mexico” session, Fifteenth
Annual International Strategic Management Society Conference, Mexico City,
October.<o:p>
</o:p>
<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
